---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Laurel Tree Counseling, LLC. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your information when you visit our website or use our telehealth services."
>
  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="accent-line mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          <strong>Effective Date:</strong> November 26, 2025<br>
          <strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 26, 2025
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary mb-8">
          Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Laurel Tree Counseling, LLC ("we," "us," "our") collects, uses, and protects information when you visit our website or use our services.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-primary-light border-l-4 border-primary p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-text-primary mt-0 mb-2">Important Distinctions</h3>
          <ul class="text-text-secondary mb-0">
            <li>This Website Privacy Policy covers information collected through our website</li>
            <li>Our HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices covers your health information and is provided separately to patients</li>
            <li>If there is any conflict, our Notice of Privacy Practices governs the use of Protected Health Information (PHI)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Who We Are</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          Laurel Tree Counseling, LLC is a telehealth mental health and nutrition counseling practice located in Michigan, providing virtual therapy and nutrition counseling services to clients throughout Michigan.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          <strong>Contact Information:</strong><br>
          Phone: <a href="tel:586-244-8087" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-hover">586-244-8087</a><br>
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@laureltreecounseling.com" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-hover">info@laureltreecounseling.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">A. Information You Provide Directly</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">When you contact us, book an appointment, or become a client, we may collect:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Contact information (name, email, phone number, mailing address)</li>
          <li>Insurance information (for billing purposes)</li>
          <li>Health information (as necessary for treatment)</li>
          <li>Payment information (processed securely through our payment processor)</li>
          <li>Demographic information (date of birth, gender, etc.)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">B. Information Collected Automatically</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">When you visit our public website, we may automatically collect:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>IP address</li>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Device type</li>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
          <li>Referring website</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          <strong>Important:</strong> We do NOT use tracking technologies on any password-protected pages or areas containing health information.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">C. Third-Party Information</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">We may receive information from:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Insurance companies (for verification and claims processing)</li>
          <li>Referring healthcare providers (with your consent)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">We use your information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li><strong>Treatment:</strong> To provide therapy and nutrition counseling services</li>
          <li><strong>Payment:</strong> To process insurance claims and billing</li>
          <li><strong>Healthcare Operations:</strong> Quality improvement, training, and administration</li>
          <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Appointment reminders and practice updates (with consent)</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> As required by law</li>
          <li><strong>Website Improvement:</strong> To analyze and improve our website functionality</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">3. How We Share Your Information</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">With Your Authorization</h3>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Other healthcare providers you designate</li>
          <li>Family members you authorize</li>
          <li>Insurance companies (for billing)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">Without Authorization (as permitted by HIPAA)</h3>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Treatment coordination with other providers involved in your care</li>
          <li>Payment processing</li>
          <li>Required legal disclosures</li>
          <li>Public health authorities (when required by law)</li>
          <li>Law enforcement (when legally required)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">Business Associates</h3>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We work with third-party service providers who assist in our operations. All business associates that handle Protected Health Information have signed Business Associate Agreements as required by HIPAA, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Our client portal provider</li>
          <li>Billing services</li>
          <li>IT support services</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">4. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">HIPAA Rights (for patients)</h3>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Right to access your health information</li>
          <li>Right to request amendments to your records</li>
          <li>Right to receive an accounting of disclosures</li>
          <li>Right to request restrictions on uses/disclosures</li>
          <li>Right to request confidential communications</li>
          <li>Right to receive a paper copy of our Notice of Privacy Practices</li>
          <li>Right to file a complaint</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text-primary mt-6 mb-3">Website Visitor Rights</h3>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Opt-out of marketing communications</li>
          <li>Request information about data we have collected</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data (where legally permissible)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">We protect your information through:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest</li>
          <li>Secure access controls and authentication</li>
          <li>Employee training on privacy and security</li>
          <li>Regular security risk assessments</li>
          <li>HIPAA-compliant telehealth platforms</li>
          <li>Incident response procedures</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We retain health records for a minimum of 7 years after your last treatment, or 7 years after a minor reaches age 18, as required by law. Website data is retained only as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We use cookies on our public marketing pages only to improve website functionality and understand how visitors use our site. We do NOT use tracking technologies on any pages that contain health information or within our secure patient portal.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">Types of cookies we use:</p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary">
          <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Necessary for basic site functionality</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors use our site (public pages only)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We do not use marketing or advertising cookies that could compromise your privacy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We provide services to individuals of all ages, including minors. For patients under 18, parental consent is required, and parents/guardians have the right to access their child's health information, subject to applicable state and federal laws regarding adolescent privacy rights.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. We will notify you of material changes by posting the updated policy on our website with a new "Last Updated" date. For changes to our Notice of Privacy Practices regarding health information, we will provide notice as required by HIPAA.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mt-10 mb-4">11. Contact Us & File a Complaint</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your privacy rights, please contact us:
        </p>
        <div class="bg-background-elevated p-6 rounded-lg my-6">
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-2">
            <strong>Laurel Tree Counseling, LLC</strong><br>
            Phone: <a href="tel:586-244-8087" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-hover">586-244-8087</a><br>
            Email: <a href="mailto:info@laureltreecounseling.com" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-hover">info@laureltreecounseling.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-text-secondary">
          You have the right to file a complaint with us or with the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services Office for Civil Rights if you believe your privacy rights have been violated. You will not be retaliated against for filing a complaint.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-background-elevated p-6 rounded-lg my-6">
          <p class="text-text-secondary mb-0">
            <strong>U.S. Department of Health and Human Services</strong><br>
            Office for Civil Rights<br>
            <a href="https://www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/complaints/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-hover">www.hhs.gov/ocr/privacy/hipaa/complaints/</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
